    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of any tree belonging to the genus Nyssa, found in North America and Asia. It is soft, light, and tough and is used in the manufacture of bridge and pier decking and construction. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
